		<div class="concept-text">
			<h4 style="color: var(--orange)">FX parameter spaces are small and well-named</h4>
			<p>An EQ band has frequency, gain, Q, and filter type. A compressor has threshold, ratio, attack, release, knee, and makeup gain. Each parameter has a name producers actually use, carrying semantic content the LLM has seen many thousands of times in tutorials and forum posts. The action space for "make this sound brighter and more punchy" is small enough that a single forward pass can land in roughly the right neighborhood, and the labels carry enough meaning that a prompt like "<em>boost 4 kHz by 3 dB</em>" maps almost trivially onto (band, freq, gain). That's a much friendlier setting than, say, predicting a 1024-d audio embedding.</p>
		</div>
	</div>

