		<div class="concept-text">
			<h4 style="color: var(--violet)">Regression vs free generation vs tool calling</h4>
			<p>There are three architectural choices for how an LLM should commit to an FX setting. <em>Regression</em> trains a head on top of the LLM that emits a continuous parameter vector. <em>Free generation</em> has the LLM emit text like "<code>EQ: 80 Hz +2 dB, 4 kHz +3 dB</code>" and parses it. <em>Tool calling</em> has the LLM emit structured JSON conforming to a registered tool schema (<code>set_eq(band=1, freq=80, gain=2)</code>). LLM2Fx is closer to free generation: text in, structured text out, with the LLM frozen. LLM2Fx-Tools is the tool-calling variant. The shift between the two papers is the whole story.</p>
		</div>
	</div>

