			<h4 style="color: var(--teal)">In-context examples come in three flavors</h4>
			<p>A useful result in LLM2Fx is that the in-context examples can be framed in three different shapes. <em>Textual</em> examples pair a description with parameter values. <em>Audio</em> examples pair perceptual features of a clip with parameter values. <em>Parametric</em> examples are parameter values on their own, anchoring the numerical scale. Each adds a different prior, and combining them lets a frozen LLM beat earlier optimization-based parameter-prediction baselines without any task-specific training. The framing matters because new effects can be added by just dropping in examples, with no retraining.</p>
		</div>
